description.narrative: Overall: To ensure that young people (YP), especially girls, and key populations are able, motivated and have the opportunity to make informed choices about their sexual and reproductive health (SRH) and that their sexual and reproductive rights are respected. Pathways: 1. YP are respected as important stakeholders in policy formulation and programs on YP SRHR 2. YP are able to make informed decisions about their SRHR 3. YP and KP are able and have the opportunity to use responsive SRH services 4. Social, cultural, legal, policy and gender barriers around YP’s and KP’s SRHR are reduced

The JeuneS3 programme is a partnership framework aligned with the Dutch SRHR policy with a focus on young people (especially girls) and key populations in francophone fragile countries or areas in Africa. The partnership will start working in Cameroon, Central African Republic and the Democratic Republic of Congo and intends to expand in the second year to Benin

Young people aged 10-24 years, with special focus on girls aged 10-14 yrs and key populations in francophone fragile countries or areas in Africa: Cameroon (Extreme North and East) , Central African Republic (CAR)) and the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) (Eastern part: North-and South Kivu) and probably in the second year Benin.
